          "body": "The second indictment narrows from the nation to the city — specifically the wealthy merchant class. Short ephahs (the dry-measure basket made smaller than legal, so customers receive less grain than they pay for, cf. Amos 8:5), false scales, deceptive weights in the bag (Deuteronomy 25:13-16 explicitly forbids), violent rich men, lying residents, deceitful tongues. Cult and commerce stand exposed as two sides of one fraud — punctilious sacrifice paid for by punctilious cheating. The verdict (6:13-15) activates the covenant curses of Deuteronomy 28:38-40: eat but not be satisfied, save but not preserve, sow but not reap, tread olives but not anoint, tread grapes but not drink. Five futile labors, each one undoing what the deceptive weights pretended to secure. The chapter closes (6:16) by naming the source code: Israel has kept the statutes of Omri and the works of Ahab — the northern dynasty whose Baalism Elijah opposed (1 Kings 16:25-33; 21:25-26). The redeemed people now resembles the dynasty Yahweh judged."
